ratings.question_text: Overall, how would you rate the workload of this course in comparison to other Yale courses you have taken?
What is your overall assessment of this course?
Do you expect to use this class for credit toward your major, or toward a pre-professional program?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: This is a very good course for cognitive science junior who do not know what to focus their senior project on. You have the opportunity to explore various fields of study in a relaxing setting.
Take this class! It's not very much work, and it will give you a better idea about what to pursue for Senior Year.
I don't think the seminar is really necessary. It's nice to meet other majors in your year, but I think other seminars with a more specific focus would probably be more stimulating.
